The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, January 11, 2003 				Metro Recommends
				 																The show				 																																	(Indian Museum, January 16 - 24)				 																																	lThe exhibition of photographs by Dr Cornelia Mallebrein focuses on gods vital in day-to-day life in India. It is divided into four sections highlighting 10 characteristic topics from Madhya Pradesh, Chhattisgarh, Karnataka and Orissa. Mrinal Sen will inaugurate the show on January 15 at 5 pm.				 																The book 				 																																	(Edited by Uma Das Gupta)				 																																	lThe book documents the remarkable relationship between Rabindranath Tagore and Edward J. Thompson through the letters they exchanged over almost 30 years. It provides insights into the personalities of both poets who met first in 1913.				 																The festival				 																																	(Swabhumi amp; other venues, January 14-19)				 																																	lThe six-day showcase will give the city a feel of Manipur in all its cultural colours. While a film festival will continue on the side, artistes will perform Kabui, Mao and Thang-ta (above) dances, courtyard theatre and recite poetry.				 																The AlBum				 																																	lThis collection of soulful Rajesh Khanna hits, mostly rendered by Kishore Kumar, is a collectors item. Part of the MusicWorld Heritage Collection, the set comprises gems like Mere Naina Sawan Bhadon and Zindagi ka Safar
